{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/gingivitis-periodontitis/how-this-topic-was-developed/evidence-exclusion-criteria/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"47be6692-bf87-5832-8dfe-c5be55c71004","slug":"evidence-exclusion-criteria","fullItemName":"Evidence exclusion criteria","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field fea7e520-5750-4932-a5fa-a7f20187b401 --><h2>Evidence exclusion criteria</h2><!-- end field fea7e520-5750-4932-a5fa-a7f20187b401 -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item a55f6228-7077-44b3-bba7-a7f20187a3cf --><!-- begin field 8a3cf987-443a-491f-af68-a7f20187b401 --><h2>Our policy</h2><!-- end field 8a3cf987-443a-491f-af68-a7f20187b401 --><!-- begin field 4d7a9659-e891-494e-b362-a7f20187b401 --><p>Scoping a literature search, and reviewing the evidence for CKS is a methodical and systematic process that is carried out by the lead clinical author for each topic. Relevant evidence is gathered in order that the clinical author can make fully informed decisions and recommendations. It is important to note that some evidence may be excluded for a variety of reasons. These reasons may be applied across all CKS topics or may be specific to a given topic.</p><p>Studies identified during literature searches are reviewed to identify the most appropriate information to author a CKS topic, ensuring any recommendations are based on the best evidence. We use the principles of the GRADE and PICOT approaches to assess the quality of published research. We use the principles of AGREE II to assess the quality of published guidelines.</p><!-- end field 4d7a9659-e891-494e-b362-a7f20187b401 --><!-- begin field 09c51f81-8fcd-4832-ad53-a7f20187b401 --><h2>Standard exclusions for scoping literature:</h2><!-- end field 09c51f81-8fcd-4832-ad53-a7f20187b401 --><!-- begin field 2404e343-5bbe-4a80-b4bc-a7f20187b401 --><ul><li>Animal studies</li><li>Original research is not written in English</li></ul><!-- end field 2404e343-5bbe-4a80-b4bc-a7f20187b401 --><!-- begin field d9878f1c-08d6-4c3c-942d-a7f20187b401 --><h2>Possible exclusions for reviewed literature:</h2><!-- end field d9878f1c-08d6-4c3c-942d-a7f20187b401 --><!-- begin field b301f587-4ff1-4de3-856a-a7f20187b401 --><ul><li>Sample size too small or study underpowered</li><li>Bias evident or promotional literature</li><li>Population not relevant</li><li>Intervention/treatment not relevant</li><li>Outcomes not relevant</li><li>Outcomes have no clear evidence of clinical effectiveness</li><li>Setting not relevant</li><li>Not relevant to UK</li><li>Incorrect study type</li><li>Review article</li><li>Duplicate reference</li></ul><!-- end field b301f587-4ff1-4de3-856a-a7f20187b401 --><!-- end item a55f6228-7077-44b3-bba7-a7f20187a3cf -->","topic":{"id":"b7a3c2c6-f067-5a2a-b5cb-565b52b08dc1","topicId":"b5c1d99b-f98a-4932-aced-7f81b69fb4ca","topicName":"Gingivitis and periodontitis","slug":"gingivitis-periodontitis","lastRevised":"Last revised in October 2018","chapters":[{"id":"cfb38419-7c7d-546b-8d5f-53e5d90275c8","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"191a777c-922f-5a14-a229-027026e22c77","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"638e02dc-c117-5dc3-9aa2-51475ec65732","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"6b07dd54-bace-502f-9276-99b0dcadf72c","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"7c3133f1-1499-5e4d-bde7-4f9ef73dffb1","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"f07ed878-39d1-558e-bdcf-a3534fbe9f72","fullItemName":"Goals and outcome measures","slug":"goals-outcome-measures","subChapters":[{"id":"fce21703-845c-5ce9-9585-48763e017d5e","slug":"goals","fullItemName":"Goals"},{"id":"691f6953-69ca-5faa-b66a-e823f1bee170","slug":"outcome-measures","fullItemName":"Outcome measures"},{"id":"f8871332-adda-5da7-97ec-504b02f786b6","slug":"audit-cr